<subSubSection id="FCE76510FFB2D555D0FA2B338FEEF89E" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B442369BFFB2D555D0FA2B338FEEF89E" blockId="1.[151,1437,868,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D0FA2B338DBFF9FE" bold="true" box="[199,461,1551,1576]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="73FD4D18FFB2D555D1EE2B2D8E22F9FE" box="[467,592,1553,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Riegeriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D1EE2B2D8E22F9FE" box="[467,592,1553,1576]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">Riegeriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D26B2B338ECDF9FE" bold="true" box="[598,703,1551,1576]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9DBA57F2FFB2D555D26B2B338ECDF9FE" box="[598,703,1551,1576]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is most similar (especially in size of the explanate lateral margins of pronotum) to the Oriental-Australian genus 
<taxonomicName id="73FD4D18FFB2D555D2922B088E80F99B" box="[687,754,1588,1613]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Iphita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D2922B088E80F99B" box="[687,754,1588,1613]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">Iphita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, species of 
<taxonomicName id="73FD4D18FFB2D555D3C92B088845F99B" box="[1012,1079,1588,1613]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Iphita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D3C92B088845F99B" box="[1012,1079,1588,1613]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">Iphita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ in the absence of sexual dimorphism (cf. 
<figureCitation id="2CC62A1EFFB2D555D1682B6B8E70F9A6" box="[341,514,1623,1648]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 24. 20 – 23" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[241,1361,224,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[230,1362,195,1900]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 24. 20 – 23 — Iphita lata sp. nov.: 20 – 21 — male, holotype, India: Tamil Nadu: Coimbatore (20 — dorsal view, 21 — ventral view), 22 – 23 — female, paratype, India: Kerala: Walayar forest (22 — dorsal view, 23 — detail of pronotum in most exposed view). 24 — Iphita coimbatorensis (Distant, 1919), female, India: Kerala: Pompa, Sabramila, detail of pronotum in most exposed view. (Photos: 20 – 22 — L. Macháčková, 23 – 24 — P. Kment)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251070/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">
Figs 
<number id="023524BCFFB2D555D1B32B648DD8F9A6" box="[398,426,1624,1648]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" value="20.0">20</number>
and 22
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2CC62A1EFFB2D555D22D2B6B8EF0F9A6" box="[528,642,1623,1648]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 29" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,193,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[164,1423,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 29. Iphita limbata Stål, 1870. 25 – 26, 28 – 29 — male, India: Arunachal Pradesh (25 — dorsal view, 26 — ventral view, 28 — procoxae, 29 — detail of procoxa, schematic). 27 — female, India: Arunachal Pradesh, dorsal view. (Photos: P. Kment)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251071/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">
25 and 
<number id="023524BCFFB2D555D2582B648EF0F9A6" box="[613,642,1624,1648]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" value="27.0">27</number>
</figureCitation>
) and procoxae lacking prominent tubercles (
<figureCitation id="2CC62A1EFFB2D555D4BD2B6B8977F9A6" box="[1152,1285,1623,1648]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 25 – 29" captionStart-1="FIGURES 30 – 34" captionStartId-0="11.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionStartId-1="12.[151,264,1651,1674]" captionTargetBox-0="[166,1422,193,1929]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1433,193,1630]" captionTargetId-0="figure@11.[164,1423,193,1932]" captionTargetId-1="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1630]" captionTargetPageId-0="11" captionTargetPageId-1="12" captionText-0="FIGURES 25 – 29. Iphita limbata Stål, 1870. 25 – 26, 28 – 29 — male, India: Arunachal Pradesh (25 — dorsal view, 26 — ventral view, 28 — procoxae, 29 — detail of procoxa, schematic). 27 — female, India: Arunachal Pradesh, dorsal view. (Photos: P. Kment)." captionText-1="FIGURES 30 – 34. Iphita limbata Stål, 1870, male, India: Arunachal Pradesh: 30 – 31 — procoxae (30 — magnification 32 ×, 31 – 47 ×); 32 – 33 — profemur (two different views: 32 – 25 ×, 33 – 18 ×); 34 — external scent efferent system and middle leg (15 ×). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 30 – 31), 1 mm (Figs 32 – 34). (SEM micrographs: P. Kment)." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/251071/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/251072/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">
Figs 
<number id="023524BCFFB2D555D4872B648977F9A6" box="[1210,1285,1624,1648]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" value="29.5" valueMax="31.0" valueMin="28.0">28–31</number>
</figureCitation>
). In addition, some other 
<taxonomicName id="73FD4D18FFB2D555D11C2B408D16F943" box="[289,356,1660,1685]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Iphita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D11C2B408D16F943" box="[289,356,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">Iphita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="73FD4D18FFB2D555D2322B418EA6F943" box="[527,724,1660,1685]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Iphita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coimbatorensis">
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D2322B418EA6F943" box="[527,724,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">I. coimbatorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="73FD4D18FFB2D555D2DB2B418F5CF943" box="[742,814,1660,1685]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Iphita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D2DB2B418F5CF943" box="[742,814,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">I. lata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9DBA57F2FFB2D555D3052B418FE4F942" box="[824,918,1661,1684]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="73FD4D18FFB2D555D3992B418864F943" box="[932,1046,1660,1685]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Iphita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbata">
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D3992B418864F943" box="[932,1046,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">I. limbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) also differ in the kidney-shaped peritreme (see 
<figureCitation id="2CC62A1EFFB2D555D17C2BA38DB3F96E" box="[321,449,1695,1720]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 17" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[196,1395,195,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[196,1396,195,1900]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 17. Ostiole and peritreme. 12 – 14 — Riegeriana apicalis (Walker, 1873), male, India: Maharashtra, Bhor Ghat: 12 — peritreme and surrounding evaporatorium (magnification 75 ×), 13 — detail of peritreme (150 ×), 14 — detail of ostiole (250 ×). 15 – 17 — Iphita limbtata Stål, 1870, male, India: Arunachal Pradesh. 15 — peritreme and surrounding evaporatorium (90 ×), 13 — detail of ostiole (250 ×), 14 — detail of peritreme (170 ×). Scale bars: 0.2 mm. (SEM micrographs: P. Kment)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251067/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">
Figs 
<number id="023524BCFFB2D555D1462BA38DB3F96E" box="[379,449,1695,1720]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" value="16.0" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="15.0">15–17</number>
</figureCitation>
) and all the femora of both sexes being ventrally provided with a longitudinal furrow distinct for most of its length (see 
<figureCitation id="2CC62A1EFFB2D555D2172BF88EDCF90A" box="[554,686,1732,1757]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1651,1674]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,193,1630]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1630]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 34. Iphita limbata Stål, 1870, male, India: Arunachal Pradesh: 30 – 31 — procoxae (30 — magnification 32 ×, 31 – 47 ×); 32 – 33 — profemur (two different views: 32 – 25 ×, 33 – 18 ×); 34 — external scent efferent system and middle leg (15 ×). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 30 – 31), 1 mm (Figs 32 – 34). (SEM micrographs: P. Kment)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251072/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">
Figs 
<number id="023524BCFFB2D555D2592BF88EDCF90A" box="[612,686,1732,1756]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" value="33.0" valueMax="34.0" valueMin="32.0">32–34</number>
</figureCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName id="73FD4D18FFB2D555D3072BF98FE6F90B" box="[826,916,1732,1757]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Iphita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D3072BF98FE6F90B" box="[826,916,1732,1757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">I. dubia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the longitudinal furrows on meso- and metafemora (observed in female) and its peritreme is more similar in shape to that of 
<taxonomicName id="73FD4D18FFB2D555D4992BD58950F8D6" box="[1188,1314,1767,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Physopelta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D4992BD58950F8D6" box="[1188,1314,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">R. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="2CC62A1EFFB2D555D50B2BDB89FDF8D6" box="[1334,1423,1767,1792]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 19" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1202,1225]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1181]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1181]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 19. Iphita dubia (Breddin, 1901), male, Indonesia: Papua: Waris (18 — dorsal view, 19 — ventral view). (Photos: L. Macháčková)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251068/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">
Fig. 
<number id="023524BCFFB2D555D54D2BD489FDF8D6" box="[1392,1423,1768,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="73FD4D18FFB2D555D0AA2A318D04F8F3" box="[151,374,1804,1829]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Riegeriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D0AA2A318D04F8F3" box="[151,374,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">Riegeriana apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
further differs from all the described species of 
<taxonomicName id="73FD4D18FFB2D555D3922A308F80F8F3" box="[943,1010,1804,1829]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Iphita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D3922A308F80F8F3" box="[943,1010,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">Iphita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the bicolorous corium with black transverse stripe on red background (see also 
<bibRefCitation id="D06C4B6AFFB2D555D2A82A138FE3F89E" author="Stehlik" box="[661,913,1839,1864]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" refString="Stehlik, J. L. &amp; Jindra, Z. (2008) New taxa of the Largidae and Pyrrhocoridae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera) from the Oriental Region. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 48, 611 - 648." type="journal article" year="2008">
Stehlík &amp; Jindra 
<number id="023524BCFFB2D555D3692A0C8FE3F89E" box="[852,913,1840,1864]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FCE76510FFB2D555D0FA2A688C8DF863" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B442369BFFB2D555D0FA2A688C8DF863" blockId="1.[151,1437,868,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D0FA2A688D74F8BB" bold="true" box="[199,262,1876,1901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">Note.</emphasis>
Similar prolonged antennae in males are known in the Afrotropical genus 
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D4A82A698886F8BA" box="[1173,1268,1877,1900]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">Kmentia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D06C4B6AFFB2D555D53C2A6889EEF8BA" author="Stehlik" box="[1281,1436,1876,1901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" refString="Stehlik, J. L. (2013) Reclassification of the genus Physopelta (Physopeltinae) and comments on the possible origin of the subfamily Larginae in the New World (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Largidae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 53, 505 - 584." type="journal article" year="2013">
Stehlík, 
<number id="023524BCFFB2D555D5592A6889EEF8BA" box="[1380,1436,1876,1900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</bibRefCitation>
(
<taxonomicName id="73FD4D18FFB2D555D0A32A4B8D75F846" box="[158,263,1911,1936]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Largidae</taxonomicName>
: Physopeltinae: Kmentiini) (
<bibRefCitation id="D06C4B6AFFB2D555D26F2A4B8E9AF846" author="Stehlik" box="[594,744,1911,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" refString="Stehlik, J. L. (2013) Reclassification of the genus Physopelta (Physopeltinae) and comments on the possible origin of the subfamily Larginae in the New World (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Largidae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 53, 505 - 584." type="journal article" year="2013">
Stehlík 
<number id="023524BCFFB2D555D2932A448E9AF846" box="[686,744,1912,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) which, however, differs markedly in the structure of male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FCE76510FFB2D556D0FA2AFC8D07FF03" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="169" pageId="1" pageNumber="168" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B442369BFFB2D556D0FA2AFC8D07FF03" blockId="1.[151,1437,868,2009]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,213]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="169" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis id="8689EA89FFB2D555D0FA2AFC8D3CF80F" bold="true" box="[199,334,1984,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">Etymology.</emphasis>
We dedicate the new genus to our dear colleague Christian Rieger, eminent 
<collectingCountry id="CCEA760BFFB2D555D4932AFC897AF80E" box="[1198,1288,1984,2008]" name="Germany" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">German</collectingCountry>
heteropterist and co-editor of the ‘Catalogue of the 
<taxonomicName id="73FD4D18FFB1D556D2782DA48EBBFF79" box="[581,713,152,175]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Heteroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Heteroptera</taxonomicName>
of the Palaearctic Region’, on the occasion of his 
<number id="023524BCFFB1D556D53D2DAB896EFF66" box="[1280,1308,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="169" value="70.0">70</number>
th birthday. Gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
